  "bib_entries": {
    "119408913": {
      "title": "A farey tail for attractor black holes",
      "abstract": "The microstates of 4d BPS black holes in IIA string theory compactified on a Calabi-Yau manifold are counted by a (generalized) elliptic genus of a (0,4) conformal field theory. By exploiting a spectral flow that relates states with different charges, and using the Rademacher formula, we find that the elliptic genus has an exact asymptotic expansion in terms of semi-classical saddle-points of the dual supergravity theory. This generalizes the known \"Black Hole Farey Tail\" of [1] to the case of attractor black holes."
    }
  },
